1
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:13,130
From now on, you don’t have to be alone anymore.

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,570
I’ll stay by your side.

3
00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:17,980
Treating us like this.

4
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,290
Do you still have enough money?

5
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,310
It’s been a while, Mai.

6
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,610
Ah, I’m so stuffed.

7
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:42,690
I told you it’s really tasty.

8
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,450
I’ve told you so many times

9
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,690
that this place is amazing.

10
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:47,539
Yeah.

11
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:49,979
You know what?

12
00:01:49,979 --> 00:01:51,500
Did you see Jun?

13
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,590
Yeah.

14
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:54,729
He’s totally my type.

15
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:58,410
His aura is insane.

16
00:01:59,030 --> 00:02:00,100
For real.

17
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:03,490
I’ve never met anyone with an aura like his.

18
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,590
I almost needed sunglasses.

19
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:07,980
I’ve got a feeling he’s talented.

20
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:12,160
His burp sounds like a melody.

21
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,790
When he picked up the pork,

22
00:02:14,230 --> 00:02:17,980
his forearms are so defined.

23
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:19,290
Oh my.

24
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:21,520
You can tell he’s been dancing his whole life.

25
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,020
Yeah, I noticed that too.

26
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:26,470
And when our eyes met, there were sparks.

27
00:02:26,470 --> 00:02:27,550
Ah!

28
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:29,440
The gaze of a main visual.

29
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,350
Isn’t that spark just your imagination?

30
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,460
Come on.

31
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:33,510
He was looking at me.

32
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:34,570
Don’t you think so, Jeng?

33
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:35,280
That look…

34
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,450
Wasn’t he looking at the pork?

35
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:37,850
Right, Yu?

36
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:40,310
You seriously don’t get it.

37
00:02:42,110 --> 00:02:43,220
Just how good is he?

38
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:45,980
Was he born to be a singer—

39
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,300
I’m gonna step outside for a bit.

40
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:47,980
Huh?

41
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:51,070
Grab some snacks for me on your way back.

42
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:52,790
Now, where were we?.

43
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:15,890
The weather’s nice today.

44
00:03:21,650 --> 00:03:23,700
It’s quite rare.

45
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,310
Mai.

46
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,230
Hm?

47
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:36,640
Are you happy being a singer?

48
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,870
Do I not look happy?

49
00:03:43,980 --> 00:03:46,710
You look happy

50
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,090
only because you have to be.

51
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,230
You smile because you have to.

52
00:03:51,829 --> 00:03:55,250
Are you really happy?

53
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,700
I am,

54
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,720
but…

55
00:04:03,130 --> 00:04:07,140
I still don’t know how to handle it.

56
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:11,030
Sometimes it doesn’t even feel real.

57
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,130
I just want you to know…

58
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:21,649
you can lean on me too.

59
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:32,640
Everything you think.

60
00:04:33,570 --> 00:04:34,740
Everything you feel.

61
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:37,030
Every bit of happiness you have.

62
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:42,540
I’ll remind you that it’s all real.

63
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:49,620
And if you need someone to lean on or vent to…

64
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:51,460
I’m here for you.

65
00:04:56,690 --> 00:04:59,770
Now we’re even. We’ve both helped each other.

66
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:06,540
Is this a dream?

67
00:05:09,690 --> 00:05:10,660
What?

68
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:14,190
I just wanted to remind you this is real.

69
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,100
Then what about how happy I am right now?

70
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,190
That’s real too.

71
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:32,600
There aren’t any stars tonight.

72
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:35,700
Of course not.

73
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:38,909
There aren’t any.

74
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:42,400
Mai.

75
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,150
Hm?

76
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,790
Since you brought your guitar…

77
00:05:45,130 --> 00:05:47,570
Can you sing me a song?

78
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:52,650
Then,

79
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:57,450
I’ll sing the song from the day we first met.

80
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:07,050
Let this loop go on and on,

81
00:06:07,050 --> 00:06:11,890
Wake up to you with every dawn

82
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:19,060
Now until eternity, I pray it’s always you

83
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:22,300
If wishes could truly come true,

84
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:25,670
I’d like to repeat this life with you

85
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:29,590
Can it please be you?

86
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:36,610
No matter how far the road may be, it’s you I’ll always see

87
00:07:30,590 --> 00:07:33,140
Is this kiss real?

88
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:36,890
I like you.

89
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:39,280
That’s real too.

90
00:08:10,780 --> 00:08:14,170
Let’s see where this leads.

91
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:18,370
I don’t want to plead,

92
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:24,540
or be your trial lover anymore.

93
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:29,980
Hearing Jun sing…

94
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:33,700
It’s like my ears have been blessed.

95
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,330
I’m not that good.

96
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:37,030
Thank you for the compliment.

97
00:08:37,570 --> 00:08:39,150
You were amazing.

98
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:41,100
And you’re humble too.

99
00:08:41,419 --> 00:08:42,940
Let’s give him a round of applause.

100
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:48,510
You’re amazing like Shining said.

101
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:54,260
This song’s gonna hit a million views.

102
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:56,410
And I’m gonna make you a star.

103
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,090
Thank you so much.

104
00:08:59,180 --> 00:09:02,900
Sometimes your timing is off.

105
00:09:02,990 --> 00:09:05,610
But remember, where there’s light,

106
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,440
you’ll be seen.

107
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:12,380
Just because you failed that day doesn’t mean you failed at life.

108
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,740
Well said.

109
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,100
Jun, clap for him.

110
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,180
You’re so extra, Jarassi.

111
00:09:23,430 --> 00:09:24,230
Ow.

112
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,230
It’s Shining.

113
00:09:26,230 --> 00:09:27,640
Yeah, Shining.

114
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:29,650
I’m used to your old name.

115
00:09:29,890 --> 00:09:32,860
How’s the marketing campaign for that label going?

116
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:34,910
Give me an update.

117
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:39,200
Bitter melon is sold out everywhere now.

118
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:42,270
Don’t worry, Jarassi— I mean, Shining,

119
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:43,760
has been killing it.

120
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:47,980
But I’m not sure if it’s helping the song or the farmers.

121
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,950
I already told Medyer

122
00:09:50,950 --> 00:09:54,420
to get her Hiwwhee Gang to help promote it.

123
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:58,860
P’Nutt Nisamanee, P’Praekwan, P’Toon,

124
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:02,730
P’Eclair and P’Erk can help push the song.

125
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:05,280
And the views are gonna skyrocket.

126
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:07,410
That’s amazing.

127
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:10,150
Keep supporting them.

128
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:14,110
And tell Medyer to report back to me if anything comes up.

129
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:15,590
-Okay?
-Okay.

130
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:27,940
Boss.

131
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:29,850
Is something wrong?

132
00:10:42,090 --> 00:10:43,020
I…

133
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:46,900
got a new song for you guys.

134
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,820
Yay!

135
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:52,050
A new song!

136
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:53,970
The song’s finished.

137
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:57,400
It’s written by a top songwriter.

138
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,320
A top songwriter?

139
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:00,310
Yes.

140
00:11:00,310 --> 00:11:03,300
I’m sure this song is gonna be a hit.

141
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:07,100
Medyer already got a famous producer on board.

142
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:09,700
We’re gonna be famous!

143
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,570
But…

144
00:11:15,460 --> 00:11:17,740
There’s something I need to tell you.

145
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:21,540
And it’s serious.

146
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:24,890
Don’t tell me you’re disbanding—

147
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:25,900
Our song...

148
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:31,780
just hit over 100k views!

149
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:34,100
Yeah!

150
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:36,900
A hundred thousand!

151
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,530
We did it!

152
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:41,260
Congrats, Mai.

153
00:11:41,460 --> 00:11:44,090
A client wants you to do a livestream.

154
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:45,100
Huh?

155
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,350
Get ready. You’re going live in ten minutes.

156
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,160
Holy shit.

157
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:52,170
You’re becoming famous.

158
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:54,120
We’re gonna make it.

159
00:11:59,080 --> 00:11:59,780
I…

160
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:05,410
I want to thank you for getting us this far.

161
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:07,900
Sean.

162
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:12,740
Thank you so much

163
00:12:13,820 --> 00:12:15,710
for always standing by my side.

164
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:18,310
From the day this label was founded

165
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:20,350
until today.

166
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,460
Thank you for supporting me.

167
00:12:31,570 --> 00:12:32,350
Fong.

168
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:36,270
Thank you for practicing so hard

169
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,600
and for coming up with the choreography.

170
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,570
I really appreciate it.

171
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:43,430
Yu.

172
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:47,170
Thank you for doing your best when you sing.

173
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,590
You started out as someone with no dream,

174
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:53,860
but I saw how hard you worked.

175
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,420
Cutter.

176
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:02,930
Thank you for being the team’s energy

177
00:13:04,410 --> 00:13:05,980
and for writing the rap verse.

178
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,130
Respect.

179
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:15,700
Jeng.

180
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:20,310
Thank you for always being by my side

181
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:27,650
and for seeing me as your big brother.

182
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,870
That means the world to me.

183
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:37,930
I know I might not be good enough.

184
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:41,390
I’ve failed

185
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,800
and made a lot of mistakes,

186
00:13:45,050 --> 00:13:48,130
but you still believe in me.

187
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:51,150
Thank you from the bottom of my heart.

188
00:13:59,830 --> 00:14:00,930
And Mai.

189
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:03,940
Thank you for being born.

190
00:14:05,530 --> 00:14:08,920
I know I might not be the best big brother.

191
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:11,690
But this big brother

192
00:14:13,610 --> 00:14:16,920
will always be here for you.

193
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:21,880
Back when you were a kid who had to face everything alone…

194
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:24,370
Do you know…

195
00:14:25,450 --> 00:14:26,940
I cried every single day.

196
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,910
But today, seeing you smile again

197
00:14:33,190 --> 00:14:34,740
makes me so happy.

198
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:41,730
(Medyer.)

199
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:42,540
Oh.

200
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:44,610
It’s Medyer.

201
00:14:44,610 --> 00:14:47,000
She’s probably calling to congratulate us.

202
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:49,300
For sure.

203
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,330
Alright, I’ll answer it.

204
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:57,790
Boss, we’ve got some trouble.

205
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:59,960
Kamikeme just dropped a new song.

206
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,600
Their new artist hit over 100k views in just one hour.

207
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:08,250
Can we at least get a love vibe?

208
00:15:08,850 --> 00:15:10,330
Isn't this our song?

209
00:15:10,330 --> 00:15:12,890
You can hold me anytime.

210
00:15:12,890 --> 00:15:13,730
Boss.

211
00:15:14,190 --> 00:15:16,590
That label hit over 100k views in less than an hour,

212
00:15:16,930 --> 00:15:18,500
but it took us a whole month.

213
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,590
Can we really make it?

214
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:21,580
Right?

215
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:23,380
Can we really do this?

216
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:29,780
Boss, you don’t need to hire some famous producer.

217
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,500
I think I get it now.

218
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:40,380
Jeng.

219
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:43,880
Jeng!

220
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:44,900
What’s gotten into him?

221
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,020
Hello.

222
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,470
Is this Ultimate Wolf agency?

223
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:27,020
Yes.

224
00:16:28,350 --> 00:16:29,550
I'm here to audition.

225
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:31,370
What's your name?

226
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,510
I'm Jeng.

227
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,740
We can start over, Jeng.

228
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,440
Let’s start again together.

229
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:33,140
This time, our song’s definitely hitting a million views.

230
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:35,770
Start over?

231
00:17:36,940 --> 00:17:38,580
And spend all your brother’s money again?

232
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:43,810
Brother?

233
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:46,450
Mhm.

234
00:17:47,910 --> 00:17:49,000
Boss Si Tian.

235
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,100
You’re Si Mai.

236
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:54,360
Boss Si Tian’s little brother.

237
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,920
Hello, Tian.

238
00:18:05,530 --> 00:18:06,470
I’m heading back.

239
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,930
Alright, I’ll come see you.

240
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:11,930
Okay. See you.

241
00:18:12,420 --> 00:18:14,650
The company’s running out of money.

242
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:16,380
What are you gonna do now?

243
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:19,410
We’ve come this far.

244
00:18:19,950 --> 00:18:21,390
We can’t quit halfway.

245
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:22,930
I have to go all in.

246
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,420
And…

247
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:27,770
What about you and Mai?

248
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:29,970
What are you gonna do?

249
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:33,940
I don’t know either.

250
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:36,970
Mai…

251
00:18:45,820 --> 00:18:46,860
Honestly,

252
00:18:47,730 --> 00:18:52,330
I don’t want to be a burden to your brother anymore.

253
00:18:54,210 --> 00:18:55,710
I’m just Jeng.

254
00:18:57,660 --> 00:18:59,000
Just an ordinary stone.

255
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,930
I’ll never be the gem your brother hoped I’d become.

256
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:07,690
But you’re the one who reignited my passion.

257
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:10,630
Because you like me.

258
00:19:15,550 --> 00:19:16,580
Can you answer me?

259
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:19,400
Everything you’ve done…

260
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,520
Was it for your dream?

261
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,670
Or was it for me?

262
00:19:32,290 --> 00:19:33,870
If you can answer that…

263
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,540
You’ll know the truth.

264
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:40,250
Whether you really love what you’re doing

265
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:43,390
or if you’ve been chasing something else.

266
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,900
My ride’s here.

267
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:50,410
I’ll get going. See you.

268
00:19:54,290 --> 00:19:55,170
Yeah.

269
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:58,850
I like you.

270
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,450
I’ve liked you for a long time.

271
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:04,070
Nice to meet you.

272
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:06,150
I hope we get to meet again at the agency.

273
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:08,270
Then I’ll go audition first.

274
00:20:12,870 --> 00:20:15,020
I love seeing you happy.

275
00:20:15,740 --> 00:20:18,950
I love watching you chase your dream.

276
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,620
I love the way you laugh at the little things.

277
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:27,310
Is it so wrong…

278
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:30,590
to love the one who filled the emptiness inside me?

279
00:20:33,790 --> 00:20:35,510
You’re my missing puzzle piece.

280
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,790
I know you can do it.

281
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:13,230
Get ready, young master.

282
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:13,850
Jeng!

283
00:21:13,850 --> 00:21:15,050
It’s almost time.

284
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,000
Jeng!

285
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,450
Young master, pull yourself together.

286
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:31,210
You can go after him as soon as the livestream is over.

287
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:44,700
Did you forget something, Jarassi?

288
00:21:49,930 --> 00:21:52,160
Have you lost your mind?

289
00:21:52,970 --> 00:21:54,410
How’d you get into my office?

290
00:21:54,820 --> 00:21:56,150
Jarassi, help!

291
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:58,860
Who’s the crazy one here?

292
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:01,610
What are you talking about?

293
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:03,330
If you’re drunk, go sleep it off.

294
00:22:03,330 --> 00:22:05,310
Don’t come barging into my office making a scene.

295
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:06,730
Is this what you want?

296
00:22:07,290 --> 00:22:08,960
Making everything I’ve built fall apart.

297
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,980
What do you mean?

298
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:12,420
Can you make some sense?

299
00:22:13,630 --> 00:22:14,750
The song.

300
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:17,220
Oh.

301
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:18,870
The song?

302
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:20,730
Yeah, that’s what I want.

303
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:23,710
A million views in one hour.

304
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,750
Why?

305
00:22:26,590 --> 00:22:28,180
Are you here asking for advice?

306
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:30,900
Or do you just want us to be fake allies?

307
00:22:33,780 --> 00:22:35,140
If you’ve a problem with me,

308
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:38,180
then hurt only me.

309
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:40,590
You can even use dirty tricks on me.

310
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:45,490
But I never thought someone sensible like you

311
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:47,700
would crush those boys’ dreams.

312
00:22:48,590 --> 00:22:50,870
What are you even talking about?

313
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:51,980
What did I do?

314
00:22:53,090 --> 00:22:53,920
Fine.

315
00:22:55,890 --> 00:22:57,140
You’re gonna deny it?

316
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:08,800
How did you get my label’s song?

317
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,350
I’m the one who should be asking that.

318
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,910
How did the song I paid for

319
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,240
end up at your label?

320
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:18,350
The only difference is one rap verse.

321
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:21,980
I just gave the boys good news today.

322
00:23:22,590 --> 00:23:26,690
Then you had Jun, Mai’s rival, release the song first.

323
00:23:26,690 --> 00:23:28,220
Happy now?

324
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:32,790
Tian.

325
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:34,230
I didn’t know anything!

326
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:36,760
I’m disappointed.

327
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:39,580
You still won’t admit what you did.

328
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:42,580
What happened to the Bai Liu I respected?

329
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:45,280
You must be so satisfied

330
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:48,230
crushing my pride.

331
00:23:49,690 --> 00:23:52,390
Are you still gonna pretend you know nothing?

332
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:54,580
Tian, just listen to me.

333
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:55,680
Listen to what?

334
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:59,190
Listen to the truth!

335
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,570
Why would I pull something that dirty?

336
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:05,000
Why would I release a song to beat yours?

337
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:07,500
I think…

338
00:24:08,350 --> 00:24:10,060
there must be some misunderstanding.

339
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,900
Hello, Medyer.

340
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,740
I messed up.

341
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:23,810
I accidentally sent the same demo file to both of you.

342
00:24:23,810 --> 00:24:26,740
Si Tian found out, so I had to confess.

343
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:30,040
If you want to fire me, I understand.

344
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:32,090
Okay.

345
00:24:38,550 --> 00:24:39,940
Tian…

346
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:43,150
I can fix this.

347
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:46,050
You can keep the same producer,

348
00:24:46,470 --> 00:24:48,130
or find a new one.

349
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:51,230
I sincerely want to help you

350
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:54,910
because I really want your label to succeed.

351
00:25:01,010 --> 00:25:02,310
For you,

352
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:05,200
I must’ve been such an idiot.

353
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:07,610
Trying to make boy groups work for so long,

354
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:09,480
and still haven’t made it.

355
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,230
I’ve lost so much money.

356
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:14,340
Yeah.

357
00:25:16,110 --> 00:25:18,040
Maybe you’re right.

358
00:25:19,940 --> 00:25:22,900
Maybe I really am the president of Ultimate Woops.

359
00:25:24,090 --> 00:25:25,630
Ultimate failure.

360
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:29,990
I never meant it like that, Tian.

361
00:25:31,050 --> 00:25:32,730
Have you had enough fun?

362
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:36,440
Can you let me go now?

363
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:41,230
At least do it for the boys who are chasing their dreams.

364
00:25:43,930 --> 00:25:45,560
If you’re still mad at me,

365
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:47,050
here.

366
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,260
Hit me.

367
00:25:49,930 --> 00:25:52,720
Get back at me for everything I did to you.

368
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,880
Go on!

369
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:59,030
Do it!

370
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:00,080
Tian!

371
00:26:01,540 --> 00:26:02,960
My label’s a joke.

372
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:06,100
I’m a loser, unlike you.

373
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:11,360
In your eyes,

374
00:26:12,180 --> 00:26:13,850
have I never been a good person?

375
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:19,000
I admit I’ve been helping you

376
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:22,260
since the day you asked for my help.

377
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,750
I’ve been helping you ever since.

378
00:26:25,850 --> 00:26:28,010
I boosted your views.

379
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:30,770
I found someone to do the PR for you,

380
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,690
I arranged food trucks for you,

381
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:35,060
I helped you find everything you needed,

382
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:38,060
You know why?

383
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:42,050
Because I wanted you to keep believing in yourself.

384
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:45,850
But if everything I’ve done

385
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:48,490
has only caused you trouble,

386
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,590
then I’m sorry.

387
00:26:59,050 --> 00:27:00,130
But you’ve never said

388
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,160
those words to me.

389
00:27:27,510 --> 00:27:28,670
I’m sorry.

390
00:27:34,730 --> 00:27:36,150
What did you just say?

391
00:27:40,410 --> 00:27:41,810
I’m a loser.

392
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:44,270
I couldn’t tell you I loved you.

393
00:27:45,620 --> 00:27:47,050
I wasn’t brave enough.

394
00:27:49,550 --> 00:27:50,730
But the truth is,

395
00:27:51,890 --> 00:27:53,190
I never lied to you.

396
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,930
I’ve liked you all this time.

397
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,320
I really, really do.

398
00:27:59,630 --> 00:28:01,840
From then until now.

399
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,080
But I was scared

400
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,830
that I wasn’t talented enough for you.

401
00:28:09,810 --> 00:28:11,960
I didn’t fall for you because you’re talented.

402
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:16,100
I like you because you have a kind heart.

403
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:19,080
You love your family

404
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,360
and care about the people around you.

405
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:24,040
That’s why I fell in love with you.

406
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:29,510
But there’s one thing I’ve been wanting to ask.

407
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:35,470
Can you love me too?

408
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:00,530
Do you have a boyfriend?

409
00:29:01,810 --> 00:29:03,090
Or are you seeing anyone?

410
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:07,910
What kind of question is that?

411
00:29:07,910 --> 00:29:08,960
Just answer me.

412
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,360
No.

413
00:29:13,780 --> 00:29:14,710
Then…

414
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,630
Will you get back together with me?

415
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:34,920
Are you okay?

416
00:29:36,580 --> 00:29:38,070
Do you want me to stop?

417
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:39,530
You know.

418
00:29:40,410 --> 00:29:41,800
Whatever’s between us…

419
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:44,120
can’t be put out so easily.

420
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:49,250
It’s just…

421
00:29:49,850 --> 00:29:51,780
your kiss is rougher than my dog.

422
00:29:53,220 --> 00:29:53,990
Good.

423
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,400
I’m looking for someone to adopt me.

424
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:05,230
Please take me home,

425
00:30:06,030 --> 00:30:07,090
Bai Liu.

426
00:31:12,450 --> 00:31:13,560
I'm here to audition.

427
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:15,640
What's your name?

428
00:31:15,770 --> 00:31:16,580
I'm Jeng.

429
00:31:17,190 --> 00:31:18,090
Fong,

430
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:19,640
please become an idol with me.

431
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,580
Deal!

432
00:31:20,580 --> 00:31:22,460
My mom said yes, okay, we can go.

433
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:25,680
You’re the one I’m looking for.

434
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,000
Please be my main vocal.

435
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:27,870
Sure.

436
00:31:28,810 --> 00:31:30,030
You’re busy looking out for others.

437
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:31,340
Try looking after yourself too.

438
00:31:32,780 --> 00:31:34,300
I hope we’ll meet again.

439
00:32:17,550 --> 00:32:21,010
Sorry, the number you've dialed cannot be connected.

440
00:32:41,810 --> 00:32:42,700
Jeng.

441
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:49,810
It’s too late now, isn’t it?

442
00:32:52,140 --> 00:32:53,700
It’s all too late now

443
00:32:54,780 --> 00:32:57,210
It’s not too late.

444
00:32:59,460 --> 00:33:00,480
Jeng just…

445
00:33:01,740 --> 00:33:03,100
needs some time.

446
00:33:07,210 --> 00:33:08,460
You just have to

447
00:33:10,300 --> 00:33:12,500
give him some space,

448
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:15,020
and give yourself some time too.

449
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:24,480
But our timing has never been right.

450
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,120
I get it.

451
00:33:29,740 --> 00:33:34,040
But there’s no such thing as bad timing.

452
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:37,210
Maybe

453
00:33:38,420 --> 00:33:43,340
you forgot to make time for yourself when you were with him.

454
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:46,300
I know that

455
00:33:47,450 --> 00:33:51,500
you were happy when you were with Jeng.

456
00:33:52,570 --> 00:33:53,480
I know that

457
00:33:55,070 --> 00:33:58,850
you laughed the hardest when you were with him.

458
00:34:00,190 --> 00:34:02,930
Every time you saw him,

459
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:05,770
all your exhaustion just melted away.

460
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:09,560
I know that

461
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:14,210
right now

462
00:34:15,530 --> 00:34:17,150
you’re hurting.

463
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,370
But like I said,

464
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:26,750
you have to give Jeng time to figure things out.

465
00:34:27,540 --> 00:34:31,570
I believe the smile he has for you

466
00:34:32,590 --> 00:34:34,159
will never fade.

467
00:34:39,100 --> 00:34:40,159
Maybe

468
00:34:41,730 --> 00:34:42,889
you need to let go for now.

469
00:34:44,690 --> 00:34:46,989
We’ll be here for you, Mai.

470
00:34:50,170 --> 00:34:51,980
If you want to cry, then cry.

471
00:34:53,210 --> 00:34:54,570
We’re right here.

472
00:34:59,210 --> 00:35:00,190
It’s okay.

473
00:35:02,090 --> 00:35:03,120
Just let it all out.

474
00:35:05,070 --> 00:35:07,510
Are you auditioning for Ultimate Wolf too?

475
00:35:08,410 --> 00:35:09,240
Mhm.

476
00:35:09,770 --> 00:35:13,590
Thank you for helping me talk about my position yesterday.

477
00:35:13,590 --> 00:35:14,740
Honestly,

478
00:35:15,220 --> 00:35:17,780
just chasing your dream is enough.

479
00:35:18,740 --> 00:35:20,220
It gives your life meaning.

480
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,680
Jeng’s coming back, right?

481
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:24,620
Yeah.

482
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,780
He’d never leave you.

483
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,160
Will he really come back?

484
00:35:30,750 --> 00:35:32,600
He definitely will.

485
00:35:33,430 --> 00:35:34,740
Just let him be for a while.

486
00:35:35,730 --> 00:35:37,770
Give him some time to sort things out.

487
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:41,810
Then he’ll come back to us.

488
00:35:47,820 --> 00:35:49,450
Bump that car for me!

489
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:50,950
Bruh.

490
00:35:50,950 --> 00:35:52,740
Pass them!

491
00:35:53,020 --> 00:35:54,850
Oh, where’d that lightning bolt come from?

492
00:35:54,850 --> 00:35:56,310
Give me a push.

493
00:35:56,310 --> 00:35:57,250
My ranking just dropped.

494
00:35:57,250 --> 00:35:58,670
We don’t have any more time.

495
00:35:59,370 --> 00:36:01,050
What’s gotten into you, Mai?

496
00:36:01,270 --> 00:36:03,370
If you’re frustrated, don’t take it out on us.

497
00:36:03,490 --> 00:36:04,910
You were so sure, Cutter.

498
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:07,430
You said Jeng will be back.

499
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,850
It’s been a whole week.

500
00:36:09,850 --> 00:36:13,370
I’ve sent him a thousand messages, and got no reply.

501
00:36:13,770 --> 00:36:14,930
I can’t even get through to him.

502
00:36:14,930 --> 00:36:15,980
Uh.

503
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:17,370
What if something happened to him?

504
00:36:17,610 --> 00:36:20,560
Maybe he’s just busy gaming like I am.

505
00:36:21,370 --> 00:36:22,810
Right there!

506
00:36:22,810 --> 00:36:24,300
Jeng’s strong.

507
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:26,140
He’ll surely come back.

508
00:36:27,780 --> 00:36:28,700
Go!

509
00:36:28,700 --> 00:36:30,270
Hey, look at this!

510
00:36:30,270 --> 00:36:31,560
Is it Jeng’s whereabouts?

511
00:36:33,170 --> 00:36:34,080
Nope.

512
00:36:34,490 --> 00:36:37,250
The clip of me and P’Sean went viral.

513
00:36:38,370 --> 00:36:41,650
I’ve got so much rizz even P’Sean can’t help but smile.

514
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:47,600
You can make him smile,

515
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:49,260
but you made your friend stop smiling.

516
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:51,680
You dummy!

517
00:36:56,430 --> 00:37:00,090
Why don’t we have Mai make a TikTok clip to find him?

518
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:02,590
This is the social media era.

519
00:37:02,590 --> 00:37:04,220
Maybe everyone online can help.

520
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:05,760
Yeah.

521
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:07,540
Good idea.

522
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:10,000
That’s brilliant.

523
00:37:10,340 --> 00:37:13,720
Mai, you should make a video

524
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:16,530
playing your guitar and singing a song to find him.

525
00:37:16,530 --> 00:37:19,180
Then use the hashtag #FindingMyJeng.

526
00:37:19,630 --> 00:37:20,730
I think it’ll work.

527
00:37:21,220 --> 00:37:23,730
I like that. I’ll help too.

528
00:37:27,370 --> 00:37:28,370
Thanks.

529
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,060
Thank you so much, guys.

530
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:35,240
Come on, Jeng’s our friend too.

531
00:37:36,740 --> 00:37:38,040
But he’s your boyfriend.

532
00:37:42,420 --> 00:37:44,490
Looks like he wants another slap.

533
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:06,590
It’s been days.

534
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:09,240
Do you have any signs of Jeng, Crayons?

535
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,050
No.

536
00:38:13,260 --> 00:38:16,380
Mai’s been so worried he hasn’t slept properly for days.

537
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:18,930
I’m worried about my little brother.

538
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:24,200
It’s okay. I’ll do everything I can to help you.

539
00:38:25,150 --> 00:38:28,520
There’s always a light at the end of the tunnel.

540
00:38:30,810 --> 00:38:33,530
You;re the best, my dear.

541
00:38:35,820 --> 00:38:39,930
I know how to fix the issue with our songs sounding similar.

542
00:38:41,430 --> 00:38:42,690
We’ll make a song together.

543
00:38:43,630 --> 00:38:44,650
How?

544
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:50,450
We’ll have artists from our labels collaborate.

545
00:38:50,450 --> 00:38:52,200
Then release a new song together.

546
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:54,700
It’ll be a whole new chapter for the music industry.

547
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:58,850
I’ll handle everything myself.

548
00:38:58,850 --> 00:39:00,200
You can rest assured.

549
00:39:02,810 --> 00:39:03,710
Really?

550
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:09,360
You deserve a reward for doing such a good job.

551
00:39:10,410 --> 00:39:13,440
Just wait till I get my hands on you, my little doe.

552
00:39:15,110 --> 00:39:16,620
I’ve been waiting.

553
00:39:23,850 --> 00:39:26,810
We’re at the office. Someone might see us.

554
00:39:27,050 --> 00:39:30,010
But last time was at the office too.

555
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:35,240
I’m off.

556
00:39:43,750 --> 00:39:45,340
(The Wolf Den)

557
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,320
Guys.

558
00:40:00,100 --> 00:40:01,640
I’ve had a crush on someone.

559
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:05,630
I used to admire his smile from afar.

560
00:40:07,870 --> 00:40:09,590
But today that smile is gone.

561
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:12,350
And I don’t know if I’ll ever see it again.

562
00:40:12,950 --> 00:40:14,790
If anyone recognizes him in the comment photo,

563
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,790
please contact me.

564
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:30,540
Just seeing your smile from afar makes me happy.

565
00:40:30,540 --> 00:40:36,520
Just watching you blush makes my heart tremble.

566
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:41,980
No need to be close, no words need to be said,

567
00:40:41,980 --> 00:40:45,020
but happy thoughts already fill my head.

568
00:40:46,810 --> 00:40:52,930
Just seeing your smile makes my heart flutter.

569
00:40:52,930 --> 00:40:58,970
I don’t want to bother you, this alone warms my heart.

570
00:40:58,970 --> 00:41:07,430
Just keeping these feelings and dreaming from afar is enough.

571
00:41:09,530 --> 00:41:10,330
Jeng.

572
00:41:11,570 --> 00:41:12,790
I miss you.

573
00:41:27,970 --> 00:41:31,480
This café is really nice.

574
00:41:31,910 --> 00:41:32,740
Whoa.

575
00:41:34,030 --> 00:41:36,390
Do they have free water here?

576
00:41:36,390 --> 00:41:37,270
Hey.

577
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:38,570
What?

578
00:41:38,890 --> 00:41:40,140
It actually worked.

579
00:41:40,140 --> 00:41:40,930
What?

580
00:41:41,150 --> 00:41:43,480
P’Mai commented on our post, P’Sopeach wished us luck,

581
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,570
and P’Blue did a dance cover of our song.

582
00:41:45,570 --> 00:41:46,310
No way.

583
00:41:47,220 --> 00:41:48,740
So we’re actually getting famous.

584
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:49,720
Yeah.

585
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:50,610
Just how?

586
00:41:50,610 --> 00:41:52,650
Maybe we’ll finally get a clue about Jeng.

587
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:53,710
Yeah.

588
00:41:54,980 --> 00:41:56,180
Could be.

589
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:57,300
Let’s check.

590
00:41:59,140 --> 00:42:01,570
Thank you so much, guys.

591
00:42:02,130 --> 00:42:05,180
Come on, what are friends for?

592
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:07,630
Yeah.

593
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:12,100
This café’s really pretty.

594
00:42:12,100 --> 00:42:13,150
Hey, hey.

595
00:42:13,730 --> 00:42:15,130
Ahem, ahem!

596
00:42:15,470 --> 00:42:17,100
Well.

597
00:42:17,310 --> 00:42:20,990
So you two are allies now, Boss?

598
00:42:21,660 --> 00:42:24,740
Wow, you’re even walking arm in arm.

599
00:42:25,390 --> 00:42:26,510
Whoa.

600
00:42:27,110 --> 00:42:27,730
Oh.

601
00:42:28,190 --> 00:42:32,590
So, why did you ask us to come here today?

602
00:42:33,870 --> 00:42:34,930
Hey.

603
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:37,230
Watch your mouth.

604
00:42:37,230 --> 00:42:38,150
Sorry, Boss.

605
00:42:38,430 --> 00:42:40,430
This is my little doe’s café.

606
00:42:41,720 --> 00:42:43,320
Little doe?

607
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:45,640
His little doe?

608
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:46,860
Enough.

609
00:42:49,750 --> 00:42:51,230
This isn’t our company.

610
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:52,490
Yes.

611
00:42:52,740 --> 00:42:55,710
We’re about to work on a big project together.

612
00:42:55,710 --> 00:42:57,160
A big project?

613
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:58,740
Yes.

614
00:42:59,390 --> 00:43:00,650
A big one.

615
00:43:00,650 --> 00:43:02,270
And we’re teaming up for it.

616
00:43:02,270 --> 00:43:03,390
It’s gonna be a success.

617
00:43:03,640 --> 00:43:05,670
That’s right, a big project.

618
00:43:06,180 --> 00:43:09,790
But first, I owe you all an apology

619
00:43:09,790 --> 00:43:11,830
for causing such a mess.

620
00:43:11,830 --> 00:43:13,030
It’s okay.

621
00:43:13,620 --> 00:43:15,380
But I’ve figured out a solution.

622
00:43:17,250 --> 00:43:20,450
I’m having both labels collaborate on a song.

623
00:43:20,450 --> 00:43:21,800
A collab?

624
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:22,740
Both labels?

625
00:43:23,660 --> 00:43:24,650
Whoa.

626
00:43:24,650 --> 00:43:26,590
Yep, a collab.

627
00:43:27,630 --> 00:43:29,110
We’re taking the released song back,

628
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,820
making a new version,

629
00:43:32,590 --> 00:43:34,300
and releasing it together.

630
00:43:35,290 --> 00:43:38,270
Artists from both labels will sing it together.

631
00:43:38,270 --> 00:43:40,280
This idea is awesome.

632
00:43:41,860 --> 00:43:43,700
Hm, Cutter.

633
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:44,460
Yes?

634
00:43:44,460 --> 00:43:46,200
You’re good at boat race commentary, right?

635
00:43:46,610 --> 00:43:48,620
Perfect for your character.

636
00:43:48,620 --> 00:43:50,430
I like that, you’re pretty talkative.

637
00:43:50,740 --> 00:43:53,210
I think I’ll add a part of you

638
00:43:53,210 --> 00:43:55,530
doing boat race commentary and rapping at the same time.

639
00:43:55,530 --> 00:43:57,830
It’ll be something totally new.

640
00:43:58,190 --> 00:44:00,370
Pretty interesting, right?

641
00:44:01,180 --> 00:44:04,010
I think it’s a good idea, boss’s darling.

642
00:44:04,010 --> 00:44:05,000
Well.

643
00:44:05,460 --> 00:44:08,380
Rapping while doing boat race commentary.

644
00:44:08,380 --> 00:44:10,970
That’s absolutely brilliant.

645
00:44:10,970 --> 00:44:12,540
It’s fresh and really interesting.

646
00:44:12,740 --> 00:44:14,050
I’m ready to get to work.

647
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:15,330
Good.

648
00:44:15,810 --> 00:44:17,000
And you.

649
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,740
My skincare queen.

650
00:44:19,340 --> 00:44:23,270
I heard you were a cover dance champion in Korea.

651
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:26,370
You’re no joke.

652
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,570
I’m giving you a solo dance break.

653
00:44:30,040 --> 00:44:33,320
I want you to shine even brighter than your glowing skin.

654
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:34,390
Whoa.

655
00:44:35,850 --> 00:44:38,370
I’d better put on five or six more layers then.

656
00:44:38,870 --> 00:44:39,610
Great.

657
00:44:40,740 --> 00:44:42,130
As for you,

658
00:44:42,130 --> 00:44:45,510
Tian said you were part of a rescue team.

659
00:44:45,510 --> 00:44:46,350
Yes.

660
00:44:46,740 --> 00:44:49,630
I’m adding a siren to the music video

661
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:51,610
to tell your background

662
00:44:51,610 --> 00:44:53,480
as part of the storytelling.

663
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:54,740
I think it’ll be interesting.

664
00:44:54,740 --> 00:44:57,140
Not bad at all.

665
00:44:57,140 --> 00:45:00,590
And Mai, I found someone to feature with you.

666
00:45:01,710 --> 00:45:02,740
Come on in.

667
00:45:03,190 --> 00:45:04,330
Who is it?

668
00:45:04,650 --> 00:45:05,510
Oh.

669
00:45:05,990 --> 00:45:07,410
It’s Jun.

670
00:45:08,210 --> 00:45:09,980
Let me officially introduce him.

671
00:45:10,310 --> 00:45:11,300
This is Jun.

672
00:45:12,130 --> 00:45:14,740
Jun and Mai are going to collaborate on a song.

673
00:45:15,860 --> 00:45:19,170
Since you both trained in Korea,

674
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:22,860
the fans are gonna love it.

675
00:45:23,100 --> 00:45:26,060
Neither of you gave up on your dreams,

676
00:45:26,060 --> 00:45:29,610
but kept going until you made it.

677
00:45:33,980 --> 00:45:36,630
So what are we waiting for?

678
00:45:36,870 --> 00:45:38,330
boss’s darling already gave the order.

679
00:45:38,330 --> 00:45:40,440
Let’s get to work.

680
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:42,430
Let’s go.

681
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:45,650
This company’s huge. I’m so jealous.

682
00:45:45,650 --> 00:45:47,110
Follow me.

683
00:45:47,110 --> 00:45:48,260
Yes, Boss.

684
00:45:55,410 --> 00:45:56,270
Mai.

685
00:45:57,690 --> 00:45:59,700
Can we talk for a moment?

686
00:46:06,180 --> 00:46:07,000
Mai.

687
00:46:07,630 --> 00:46:08,580
How’ve you been?

688
00:46:10,040 --> 00:46:10,990
I’ve been good.

689
00:46:12,740 --> 00:46:13,820
How about you?

690
00:46:14,630 --> 00:46:16,580
I’ve been good too.

691
00:46:19,260 --> 00:46:20,020
So…

692
00:46:20,430 --> 00:46:22,410
How’s our group doing?

693
00:46:23,620 --> 00:46:25,880
I was really surprised to see you.

694
00:46:26,970 --> 00:46:30,280
I was surprised too.

695
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:31,790
Er…

696
00:46:31,790 --> 00:46:33,500
Our group didn’t make it.

697
00:46:34,220 --> 00:46:35,020
Huh?

698
00:46:36,630 --> 00:46:39,690
Did the label drop our group?

699
00:46:40,610 --> 00:46:44,100
They said we didn’t have enough potential,

700
00:46:44,100 --> 00:46:45,640
so they canceled it.

701
00:46:53,660 --> 00:46:54,900
It wasn’t because of me, was it?

702
00:46:55,370 --> 00:46:56,040
Hey.

703
00:46:56,370 --> 00:46:58,510
No, don’t think like that.

704
00:46:59,660 --> 00:47:00,580
Can I ask you something?

705
00:47:00,580 --> 00:47:01,350
Hm?

706
00:47:02,340 --> 00:47:03,570
Back when I ran away,

707
00:47:04,980 --> 00:47:06,010
were you mad at me?

708
00:47:08,190 --> 00:47:09,180
No.

709
00:47:11,420 --> 00:47:14,210
I believed you had your reasons.

710
00:47:14,740 --> 00:47:19,350
Good reasons for leaving.

711
00:47:20,740 --> 00:47:21,610
Anyway,

712
00:47:22,450 --> 00:47:25,350
I’m glad you didn’t give up on your dream.

713
00:47:28,550 --> 00:47:29,710
Don’t overthink it.

714
00:47:30,030 --> 00:47:31,400
I should be thanking him.

715
00:47:31,990 --> 00:47:34,230
He made me dream again.

716
00:47:34,740 --> 00:47:35,770
Him?

717
00:47:36,370 --> 00:47:37,240
Who?

718
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,070
Never mind.

719
00:47:38,620 --> 00:47:39,530
Mai.

720
00:47:39,790 --> 00:47:43,070
I never told P’Bai Liu or your brother that you ran away.

721
00:47:43,310 --> 00:47:44,250
So don’t worry.

722
00:47:44,250 --> 00:47:45,170
Thanks.

723
00:47:45,530 --> 00:47:47,070
Are you Mai?

724
00:47:48,440 --> 00:47:49,330
Yes.

725
00:47:49,800 --> 00:47:52,200
Last night, I saw your video on TikTok.

726
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,740
Then my friend sent me this.

727
00:47:54,740 --> 00:47:56,930
Is this the person you’re looking for?

728
00:47:58,310 --> 00:48:00,200
Yeah!

729
00:48:00,740 --> 00:48:01,910
Yes, that’s him.

730
00:48:01,910 --> 00:48:03,890
Where’s your friend now?

731
00:48:03,890 --> 00:48:06,470
She’s teaching kids in Chiang Dao.

732
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:09,230
Chiang Dao?

733
00:48:09,770 --> 00:48:10,870
Chiang Dao?

734
00:48:12,740 --> 00:48:13,490
Wait.

735
00:48:14,070 --> 00:48:15,870
What the heck is he doing there?

736
00:48:16,570 --> 00:48:17,670
That’s so far away.

737
00:48:17,900 --> 00:48:18,740
Wait.

738
00:48:19,210 --> 00:48:21,970
Did he become a monk and go meditate?

739
00:48:21,970 --> 00:48:23,660
No way.

740
00:48:24,740 --> 00:48:28,060
He’s probably just waiting for someone to come find him.

741
00:48:28,740 --> 00:48:30,140
This is like A Tale of Thousand Stars.

742
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:31,330
Hey.

743
00:48:32,030 --> 00:48:35,170
Fong, just how many BL series have you watched?

744
00:48:36,130 --> 00:48:36,970
Oh.

745
00:48:37,210 --> 00:48:40,270
Maybe Jeng time traveled like in Love Upon a Time.

746
00:48:40,470 --> 00:48:42,620
Or maybe he’s got a bodyguard.

747
00:48:44,330 --> 00:48:45,800
I’ve heard enough.

748
00:48:46,620 --> 00:48:47,700
Seriously,

749
00:48:47,810 --> 00:48:50,040
you should get your brain checked.

750
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:51,770
You’re getting more ridiculous every day.

751
00:48:51,770 --> 00:48:52,920
Then you’re coming with me.

752
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:56,010
What if he really quits the group?

753
00:48:57,660 --> 00:48:58,740
What are you gonna do?

754
00:48:59,890 --> 00:49:01,250
I’m leaving tonight.

755
00:49:01,410 --> 00:49:02,210
Tonight?

756
00:49:03,150 --> 00:49:04,250
Why not wait until tomorrow?

757
00:49:05,010 --> 00:49:06,500
I can’t wait anymore.

758
00:49:07,320 --> 00:49:08,590
I won’t be able to sleep.

759
00:49:10,370 --> 00:49:11,580
Go, Mai.

760
00:49:12,090 --> 00:49:13,600
Bring our group member home.

761
00:49:14,550 --> 00:49:18,580
The one who made your dream come true.

762
00:49:20,100 --> 00:49:22,990
Bring him back, Mai.

763
00:49:23,340 --> 00:49:26,350
Tian and I will handle things here. Don’t worry.

764
00:49:26,740 --> 00:49:29,020
Just come back ready to work.

765
00:49:29,380 --> 00:49:30,430
Good luck.

766
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:34,380
I’ll contact the rescue team.

767
00:49:34,940 --> 00:49:37,660
Maybe they have Jeng’s location.

768
00:49:41,480 --> 00:49:43,150
Thanks, everyone.

769
00:49:44,030 --> 00:49:44,740
Alright.

770
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,480
Let’s get everything ready first,

771
00:49:47,860 --> 00:49:50,120
so we’ll be ready when Jeng comes back.

772
00:49:53,620 --> 00:49:55,190
Go bring your boyfriend home.

773
00:50:15,050 --> 00:50:16,130
Are we here?

774
00:50:16,130 --> 00:50:17,940
Yep.

775
00:50:17,940 --> 00:50:20,380
This is the place, right?

776
00:50:20,380 --> 00:50:21,190
Yeah.

777
00:50:21,190 --> 00:50:23,500
I remember it because

778
00:50:23,880 --> 00:50:28,740
I dropped him off here about two weeks ago.

779
00:50:28,740 --> 00:50:32,270
His phone fell into the water, so I took it to get fixed for him.

780
00:50:32,510 --> 00:50:36,440
He teaches kids around here.

781
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:37,560
That’s why I remember.

782
00:50:37,560 --> 00:50:40,140
Is it hard to find someone here?

783
00:50:40,140 --> 00:50:44,740
No, everyone in the village knows each other

784
00:50:44,740 --> 00:50:47,160
because the houses are all close together.

785
00:50:47,550 --> 00:50:48,570
Thank you so much.

786
00:50:49,030 --> 00:50:50,220
-Good luck.
-Thanks.

787
00:50:53,290 --> 00:50:54,020
First move.

788
00:50:55,050 --> 00:50:55,810
Point.

789
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:57,850
Switch sides.

790
00:50:59,130 --> 00:50:59,980
Cross your arms.

791
00:51:02,120 --> 00:51:03,080
Three times.

792
00:51:04,100 --> 00:51:05,030
Point your finger up.

793
00:51:05,890 --> 00:51:06,740
Cross again.

794
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:11,960
Left, right.

795
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:13,850
Cross your arms like this.

796
00:51:15,160 --> 00:51:21,030
Ever since you walked into my life, my world changed overnight

797
00:51:21,030 --> 00:51:22,130
Please don't disappear again.

798
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:25,850
I wish time would slow down.

799
00:51:27,030 --> 00:51:29,210
I want you by my side.

800
00:51:32,060 --> 00:51:33,470
Please don’t disappear again.

801
00:51:42,740 --> 00:51:44,270
I’ll never disappear.

802
00:51:45,340 --> 00:51:46,590
Time stopped…

803
00:51:47,830 --> 00:51:49,110
the moment I met you.

804
00:52:02,740 --> 00:52:10,740
Kiss him! Kiss him!

805
00:52:12,340 --> 00:52:17,320
I’ll choose the path with you, every single time

806
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:20,630
Let this loop go on and on,

807
00:52:20,630 --> 00:52:25,510
Wake up to you with every dawn

808
00:52:25,510 --> 00:52:33,050
Now until eternity, I pray it’s always you

809
00:52:33,050 --> 00:52:36,090
If wishes could truly come true,

810
00:52:36,090 --> 00:52:39,420
I’d like to repeat this life with you

811
00:52:39,420 --> 00:52:43,400
Can it please be you?

812
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:52,190
No matter how far the road may be, it’s you I’ll always see

813
00:52:53,100 --> 00:52:59,140
From now until forever, my heart will always be yours
